svg.desc:
Lissajous-curves
left-top: f/f=1 phi=0 center-top: f/f=1 phi=pi/2 right-top: f/f=1 phi=pi/4 left-bottom: f/f=2/1 phi=0 center-bottom: f/f=3/2 phi=0 right-bottom: f/f=4/3 phi=0
plotted with several adapted cubic bezier-curves The plotcurves were calculated by some fancy code. The bezier-curve controlpoints are placed on tangents of the function-curve. They are furthermore positioned in a way to minimize the average quadratic distance between the bezier-curve and the function. This gives an accuracy, so that the deviation is in no point greater than 0.000001.
